
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee <|-- Employee
class Director <|-- CreativeEmployee
class Actor <|-- CreativeEmployee

class Technician <|-- Employee
- fieldOfActivity: String

class FilmSet {
  - location: String
}

class Film {
  - title: String
  - yearOfRelease: Integer
  - genre: String (enum: thriller, action, horror, comedy)
}

class Screenwriter {
  - name: String
  - mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  - title: String
  - version: Integer
  - date: Date
  - numberOfScenes: Integer
  - plot: String
  - basedOn: String (enum: novel, concept)
}

class Novel {
  - title: String
  - author: String
}

' Relationships
Employee "1" *-- "0..*" Film: worksOn
Director "1" -- "1" Film: directs
Actor "1" -- "0..*" Film: actsIn
Technician "1" -- "0..*" Film: worksOn

FilmSet "1" -- "0..*" Film: usedFor
Screenwriter "1" -- "0..*" Screenplay: writes
Screenplay "1" -- "1" Film: usedFor
Screenplay "1" -- "0..1" Novel: basedOn

Actor "1" -- "1" OscarWinner: hasOscar
Director "1" -- "1" OscarWinner: hasOscar

class OscarWinner {
  - hasOscar: Boolean
}
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Employee** is a base class with common attributes (`name`, `socialSecurityNumber`).
- **CreativeEmployee** inherits from `Employee`. It includes **Director** and **Actor**.
- **Actor** has an attribute for education and a reference to their **Oscar status**.
- **Director** has an assistant's name as an attribute.
- **Technician** is another type of employee with a `fieldOfActivity`.
- **FilmSet** has a location and can be used for multiple **Films**.
- **Film** has a title, release year, and genre.
- **Screenwriter** stores their name and most successful film.
- **Screenplay** has details like title, version, scenes, etc., and it's linked to one **Novel** or **Concept**.
- **Screenplay** is used by exactly one **Film**.
- **OscarWinner** is a helper class that holds whether a person has won an Oscar.

